If they do not have a physical or have one signed before July 1, 2019, they will need a new one. Once JH coaches get an idea of which kids are interested in their sport, information will be put out about meetings close to the start of school.

With the state changing the playoff format and one of our district opponents cancelling their season, we have been forced to revise our football schedule. New schedule is as follows.

AWAY -- Friday, August 28th -- Wayne @ Central Decatur (7:00 pm)
HOME -- Friday, September 4th -- Cardinal @ Wayne (7:00 pm)
Friday, September 11th -- BYE
AWAY -- Friday, September 18th -- Wayne @ Madrid (7:00 pm)
HOME-- Friday, September 25th -- Nodaway Valley @ Wayne (7:00)
HOME -- Friday, October 2nd -- Ogden @ Wayne (7:00 pm)
AWAY -- Friday, October 9th -- Wayne @ Earlham (7:00 pm)
TBD -- Friday, October 16th -- 1st round of playoffs

Wayne will be guaranteed to play in the 1st round of the playoffs, the location and opponent will be determined at a later date.

Here is a link to the new revised schedule and playoff format.
https://www.iahsaa.org/football-2020-revised-schedule/

Dear Wayne Community:

Beginning today, June 25, 2020, social gatherings on school grounds including the parking lots at Wayne CSD high school will not be permitted after school hours or events. This change is due to activity that has occurred this past week. The most recent events that have occurred in the Wayne CSD parking lot do not represent FALCON PRIDE! Anyone in violation will be subject to citations issued by law enforcement. In closing, I would ask that everyone respect the school and community and show FALCON PRIDE!

Sincerely,

Mike Still, Superintendent
Wayne CSD

post_text:
The Falcon Foundation is an endowment fund that was created in collaboration with the Community Foundation in Wayne County. The purpose of the fund is to provide resources for needs of the school district and its students. The Falcon Foundation has provided scholarship funds for Wayne Community seniors for the past three years, and we plan to increase the amount of funding available. We would like for you to be a part of this! As we near the end of the calendar year, please consider a tax deductible donation to the Falcon Foundation. There are several categories of giving but any and all gifts will be appreciated.

Please contact Cindy Comer in the central office at Wayne Community, cindy.comer@wayne.k12.ia.us or Dave Daughton at dave.daughton@gmail.com for information or to donate. And...if you have already donated, you can donate again!!

Please share.
